C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2FDSC01286_11zon-1697801665.jpg%20675w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2FDSC01286_11zon-1697801665-300x225.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2FDSC01286_11zon-1697801665-500x375.jpg%20500w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2FDSC01286_11zon-1697801665-150x112.jpg%20150w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-332692%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22506%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%20class%3D%5C%22wp-element-caption%5C%22%3EThe%20locals%20in%20Jalna%20contributed%20their%20bit%20by%20providing%20the%20diesel.%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%20%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3EJalna%E2%80%99s%20transformation%3A%20From%20250%20tankers%20a%20day%20to%20nil%3C%2Fh2%3E%20%3Cp%3EHer%20NGO%2C%20headquartered%20in%20Ahmedabad%2C%20provided%20the%20rental%20costs%20of%20the%20expensive%20machines%20required%20for%20the%20job%20through%20its%20partnership%20with%20the%20A.T.E.%20Chandra%20foundation%20in%20Mumbai%2C%20while%20the%20locals%20contributed%20their%20bit%20by%20providing%20the%20diesel.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EHer%20team%20worked%20to%20make%20sure%20it%20translated%20into%20results%20on%20the%20ground.%20Although%20her%20NGO%20had%20been%20set%20up%20many%20years%20ago%20with%20the%20purpose%20of%20focussing%20on%20animal%20care%2C%20it%20had%2C%20in%20fact%2C%20primarily%20focussed%20on%20saving%20and%20improving%20human%20lives%20in%20a%20country%20prone%20to%20natural%20and%20manmade%20calamities%20where%20government%20intervention%20is%20often%20inadequate%20or%20even%20absent.%20Human%20beings%2C%20at%20some%20level%2C%20took%20precedence.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EWhen%20Nutanben%20and%20her%20team%20began%20working%20in%20around%20330-odd%20villages%20and%20%3Cem%3Etalukas%3C%2Fem%3E%20that%20comprise%20the%20Jalna%20district%2C%20the%20situation%20was%20not%20much%20better%20than%20it%20was%20in%20Beed.%20Water%20was%20very%20scarce%2C%20most%20of%20the%20water%20bodies%20in%20the%20region%20were%20silted%20up%20or%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thebetterindia.com%2F288219%2Fafter-visiting-drought-prone-villages-23-yo-plants-3-lakh-trees-in-three-years%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ebone%20dry%20%3C%2Fa%3Eand%20tankers%20were%20the%20only%20way%20of%20life.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EWhen%20they%20started%20working%2C%20each%20%3Cem%3Etehsil%3C%2Fem%3E%20%E2%80%94%20there%20are%208%20in%20Jalna%20district%20%E2%80%94%20survived%20on%20250%20tankers%20per%20day.%20Farmers%20were%20barely%20producing%20anything%20since%20there%20was%20no%20water%20for%20farming%3B%20meeting%20the%20basic%20consumption%20needs%20was%20a%20struggle.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EMoreover%2C%20when%20the%20team%20arrived%20in%20the%20district%2C%20villagers%20and%20locals%20were%20highly%20sceptical%20on%20whether%20such%20work%20could%20be%20done%20with%20community%20participation%20and%20through%20the%20efforts%20of%20an%20NGO.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CIt%20was%20primarily%20seen%20as%20work%20only%20the%20government%20could%20do%2C%E2%80%9D%20explains%20Narayan%20Devkate%2C%2055%2C%20a%20farmer%20in%20Pimparkhed%2C%20who%20tends%20to%20his%2050-acre%20land%20parcel%20with%20his%20two%20brothers.%20Of%20the%20117-odd%20villages%20in%20his%20vicinity%2C%2078%20had%20no%20water%20at%20all%20when%20the%20effort%20began%2C%20he%20adds.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EPainstakingly%20and%20with%20gentle%20but%20persistent%20persuasion%2C%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thebetterindia.com%2F280255%2Ftamil-nadu-village-pond-revival-malarvizhli-akka-inspiring-water-conservation%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ethe%20work%20began%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20ranged%20from%20desilting%20and%20rejuvenating%20small%20ponds%2C%20recharging%20borewells%2C%20%3Cem%3Enaali%20kholikaran%20%3C%2Fem%3E(veins%20of%20the%20river%20that%20have%20got%20filled%20with%20silt%20and%20turned%20dry)%20and%20compartment%20bunding.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAs%20a%20result%2C%20a%20total%20of%20427%20km%20of%20nullahs%20have%20been%20opened%2C%2019%20ponds%20have%20been%20brought%20back%20to%20life%20and%20a%20total%20of%2079%2C7443%20cubic%20metres%20of%20silt%20has%20been%20removed%20and%20carted%20in%20the%20last%206-7%20years.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EOver%20the%20last%20four%20years%2C%20work%20has%20started%20on%20cleaning%20and%20rejuvenating%20the%2020%20km%20Kundalika%20and%20Seena%20river%2C%20of%20which%20around%205%20km%20has%20been%20done%20so%20far%20and%20a%20total%20of%20900%2C000%20lakh%20cubic%20metre%20of%20silt%20and%20a%20total%20of%20405%2C000%20cubic%20metre%20of%20garbage%20has%20been%20pulled%20out%20and%20carted!%20To%20see%20the%20river%20flowing%2C%20even%20if%20only%20in%20part%2C%20gave%20Nutanben%20and%20her%20team%20a%20spark%20of%20joy%20that%20only%20a%20few%20other%20things%20could%20manage!%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EBut%20what%20is%20perhaps%20only%20joy%20and%20satisfaction%20for%20the%20NGO%20team%20working%20on%20the%20ground%2C%20it%20is%20a%20matter%20of%20a%20far%20better%20quality%20of%20life%20for%20the%20farmers%20and%20the%20community%20living%20there.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ELaxman%20Sawade%20was%20growing%20around%20five%20quintals%20of%20cotton%20every%20year%20on%20his%20seven%20acre%20farm%20and%20barely%20managing%20to%20make%20ends%20meet.%20In%202013%2C%20he%20took%20the%20initiative%20of%20applying%20300%20trollies%20of%20silt%20on%20three%20acres%20of%20his%20land.%20Not%20only%20has%20his%20cotton%20output%20gone%20up%2C%20he%20is%20also%20growing%20grapes%20on%20his%20land%20since.%20Overall%2C%20his%20income%20has%20jumped%20to%20Rs%2015%20lakh%20a%20year%2C%20helping%20him%20build%20a%20better%20home%2C%20buy%202.5%20additional%20acres%20of%20land%2C%20a%20tractor%20and%20a%20motorbike.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EOverall%2C%20the%20notion%20that%20almost%20nothing%20brings%20more%20prosperity%20and%20hope%20than%20water%20security%20has%20been%20amply%20reinforced%20by%20Jalna.%20Devkate%20says%20that%20three%20new%20factories%20have%20come%20up%20in%20the%20area%2C%20including%20a%20water%20intensive%20sugarcane%20factory%2C%20leading%20to%20new%20employment%20opportunities%20in%20the%20district.%20In%20a%20region%20that%20has%20been%20bereft%20of%20almost%20any%20work%20opportunities%2C%20this%2C%20he%20argues%2C%20is%20what%20has%20helped%20bring%20in%20more%20and%20more%20takers%20for%20the%20ongoing%20efforts.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cfigure%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-image%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20806px)%20100vw%2C%20806px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F20170307_113448_11zon-1697801692.jpg%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22806%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22When%20the%20team%20arrived%20in%20the%20district%2C%20villagers%20and%20locals%20were%20highly%20sceptical%20on%20whether%20such%20work%20could%20be%20done%20with%20community%20participation%20and%20through%20the%20efforts%20of%20an%20NGO.%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F20170307_113448_11zon-1697801692.jpg%20806w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F20170307_113448_11zon-1697801692-300x225.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F20170307_113448_11zon-1697801692-500x375.jpg%20500w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F20170307_113448_11zon-1697801692-768x576.jpg%20768w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F20170307_113448_11zon-1697801692-150x112.jpg%20150w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-332695%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22604%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%20class%3D%5C%22wp-element-caption%5C%22%3EWhen%20the%20team%20arrived%20in%20the%20district%2C%20villagers%20and%20locals%20were%20highly%20sceptical%20on%20whether%20such%20work%20could%20be%20done%20with%20community%20participation%20and%20through%20the%20efforts%20of%20an%20NGO.%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%20%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3EMaking%20PPP%20work%3A%20Samast%20Mahajan%2C%20A.T.E.%20Chandra%20Foundation%20and%20more%3C%2Fh2%3E%20%3Cp%3EFor%20all%20those%20lamenting%20the%20failure%20of%20public%20and%20private%20partnerships%20in%20India%2C%20the%20water%20rejuvenation%20efforts%20of%20Maharashtra%20offers%20a%20beacon%20of%20hope.%20It%20was%20in%202013%20that%20Bain%20Capital%20chairman%20Amit%20Chandra%20%E2%80%94%20who%20set%20up%20and%20finances%20the%20A.T.E.%20Chandra%20foundation%20%E2%80%94%20and%20his%20wife%2C%20Archana%2C%20started%20questioning%20why%20despite%20a%20lot%20of%20talk%20and%20bluster%2C%20farmer%20suicides%20in%20the%20drought-hit%20state%20refused%20to%20abate.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIt%20didn%E2%80%99t%20take%20rocket%20science%20to%20reach%20a%20quick%20answer-%20poor%20rainfall%20%3D%20failed%20crop%20season%20%3D%20farmer%20debt%20%3D%20farmer%20suicide.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThat%E2%80%99s%20when%20they%20came%20across%20another%20NGO%20already%20working%20on%20the%20simple%20model%20they%20have%20since%20adopted-%20silt%20removal%20and%20rejuvenation%20of%20water%20bodies.%20Primary%20research%20done%20by%20them%20showed%20that%20there%20are%20many%20water%20bodies%20across%20the%20country%20that%20have%20over%20the%20years%20become%20defunct%20or%20unable%20to%20hold%20much%20water%20due%20to%20heavy%20silting.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20groundwater%20too%20fails%20to%20get%20recharged%20as%20the%20silt%20prevents%20the%20rainwater%20from%20reaching%20the%20bottom.%20But%20if%20someone%20removed%20the%20silt%2C%20the%20water%20body%20could%20be%20rejuvenated%20and%20even%20better%20the%20silt%20%E2%80%94%20which%20is%20usually%20quite%20fertile%20%E2%80%94%20could%20be%20used%20by%20farmers%20on%20their%20land%20to%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thebetterindia.com%2F268059%2Fmeena-pawar-nashik-farmer-earns-lakhs-grape-debt-farming-success-story-inspiring%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eimprove%20productivity%3C%2Fa%3E.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EFrom%202016%20to%202019%2C%20the%20A.T.E%20CF%2C%20along%20with%2022-odd%20partner%20organisations%2C%20worked%20extensively%20in%20Maharashtra%20to%20rejuvenate%20over%202%2C700%20water%20bodies%2C%20impacting%20around%204%2C200%20villages.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20COVID-19%20pandemic%20dampened%20their%20efforts%20but%20did%20not%20stop.%20In%202020%20and%202021%2C%20work%20continued%20in%20Rajasthan%20and%20Karnataka.%20In%202022%2C%20the%20work%20picked%20up%20pace%20once%20again%20and%20916%20water%20bodies%20were%20rejuvenated%20in%2018%20districts%20of%20Maharashtra%2C%20Rajasthan%2C%20Uttar%20Pradesh%2C%20Madhya%20Pradesh%2C%20some%20at%20the%20behest%20of%20Niti%20Aayog%20which%20had%2C%20by%20then%2C%20pulled%20in%20by%20the%20foundation.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cfigure%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-image%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20768px)%20100vw%2C%20768px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2FWhatsApp-Image-2023-10-17-at-10.00.31_11zon-1697801718.jpeg%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22768%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%20India%20is%20placed%20at%20120th%20amongst%20122%20countries%20in%20the%20water%20quality%20index%2C%20with%20nearly%2070%25%20of%20water%20being%20contaminated.%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2FWhatsApp-Image-2023-10-17-at-10.00.31_11zon-1697801718.jpeg%20768w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2FWhatsApp-Image-2023-10-17-at-10.00.31_11zon-1697801718-300x225.jpeg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2FWhatsApp-Image-2023-10-17-at-10.00.31_11zon-169780171